#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1125
msgid "Advanced"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1126
msgid "By default, uninstalling Indigetal Media Offload for Bunny.net preserves offload-critical WordPress data: saved settings, encrypted credentials, Storage manifests, Stream attachment metadata, and URL rewriting state. You normally do not need to change anything here."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1129
msgid "Warning:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1130
msgid "Only enable the option below if you intend to remove plugin-owned WordPress data when the plugin is uninstalled. This does not delete local media files from your server and does not delete remote objects in Bunny Storage or Bunny Stream."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1136
msgid "Remove plugin-owned WordPress data on uninstall"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1158
msgid "When enabled, uninstall removes this plugin's saved settings and the WordPress-stored offload data it relies on (credentials, manifests, Stream-related attachment metadata, and similar), then clears this opt-in so it does not remain after removal. When disabled, that data is kept so you can reinstall. In both cases, uninstall performs a small amount of internal cleanup so WordPress does not keep scheduled work pointing at removed plugin code. Local media files on your server and content stored at Bunny.net are never deleted by this setting."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1181
msgid "Bunny.net external service"
msgstr ""

#. translators: 1: Bunny terms URL, 2: Bunny privacy URL
#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1186
#, php-format
msgid "Indigetal Media Offload for Bunny.net sends media and configuration-related data to <strong>Bunny.net</strong> only when you enable Stream and/or Storage features and use the workflows this plugin provides. Review Bunny.net’s <a href=\"%1$s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Terms of Service</a> and <a href=\"%2$s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">privacy policy</a> before enabling offload."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1198
msgid "Data sent to Bunny.net"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1199
msgid "Depending on what you enable, the plugin may send the following kinds of data to Bunny.net:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1202
msgid "Stream (when enabled): the server makes requests to Bunny Stream API hosts such as video.bunnycdn.com to create, update, inspect, and delete videos and collections. Playback-related URLs may use hostnames such as player.mediadelivery.net and the Stream Pull Zone hostname you configure in settings."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1203
msgid "Storage (when enabled): the server makes requests to the regional Bunny Storage API host for the zone you select, and public file URLs use the Storage Pull Zone hostname you configure."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1204
msgid "API keys, passwords, zone identifiers, and related options are stored in the WordPress database (encrypted where this plugin applies encryption) and are used only to contact Bunny services on your behalf."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1210
msgid "Admin help links"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1211
msgid "On the Settings tab, help text may link to Bunny.net documentation on docs.bunny.net, the customer dashboard on dash.bunny.net, a support article on support.bunny.net, and CDN product pages used to explain pull-zone hostnames. Opening those links is optional; they remain under Bunny.net’s terms and privacy policy linked above."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1217
msgid "Delivery scope in Free"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1218
msgid "This Free release does not generate HMAC-signed or token-authenticated CDN URLs from PHP for Storage or Stream."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1219
msgid "This Free release does not include operator Tools tabs, bulk batch or retry queues, a block-based Stream upload experience, or resumable chunked video uploads."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1220
msgid "Whether URLs are publicly readable or restricted is determined by your Bunny Pull Zone, Storage, and Stream configuration outside WordPress."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1226
msgid "Local media files after offload"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1227
msgid "On the Settings tab, separate toggles control whether local media files are removed from this server after successful Storage offload and after successful Stream video offload. When a toggle is enabled, WordPress may no longer have a local file behind the attachment URL even though delivery continues from Bunny.net."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1233
msgid "Remote Bunny objects when you delete attachments"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1234
msgid "Deleting a WordPress attachment for media that was offloaded to Bunny Storage or Bunny Stream may delete the corresponding remote Bunny object where that behavior is implemented, so visitors should not retain a working hotlink to the removed object."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1240
msgid "Uninstall and data retention"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1241
msgid "By default, uninstall keeps this plugin’s settings, saved credentials, offload records, and media-related metadata in WordPress so you can reinstall and keep using media already stored at Bunny.net."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1242
msgid "Unless you turn on Advanced → Remove plugin-owned WordPress data on uninstall on the Settings tab (and only if you intend to wipe that data), nothing in that list is removed on uninstall."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1243
msgid "Uninstall never deletes your site’s media files on disk or removes objects in your Bunny Storage zones or Stream library."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1244
msgid "When that Advanced option is enabled, uninstall removes this plugin’s saved settings and the WordPress-stored offload data it relies on, then clears the opt-in so it does not remain after removal; local media files and Bunny.net objects are still never deleted by the plugin."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1245
msgid "A small amount of internal cleanup always runs on uninstall so WordPress does not keep scheduled work pointing at removed plugin code."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1251
msgid "Optional Pro companion"
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: URL to author / Pro addon commercial information.
#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1256
#, php-format
msgid "A Pro addon is available to extend this Free base plugin with additional operator workflows and delivery features—such as token-compatible URL delivery. For availability and feature details, visit <a href=\"%s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Indigetal WebCraft</a>."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1265
msgid "This Free plugin does not bundle that companion, surface off–WordPress.org update prompts for it in wp-admin, or require it for core Media Library Storage and Stream offload."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1271
msgid "Create a Bunny.net account"
msgstr ""

#. translators: 1: Affiliate signup URL (bunny.net with ref), 2: Bunny affiliate program documentation URL
#: includes/Admin/BunnySettings.php:1276
#, php-format
msgid "If you need a Bunny.net account, you can <a href=\"%1$s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer sponsored\">open bunny.net with this affiliate link</a>. This is an affiliate link; if you become a paying customer, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. Bunny publishes its affiliate rules in the <a href=\"%2$s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">affiliate program documentation</a>."
msgstr ""

